ğŸ§© 1. INTRODUCTION

A Quiz Game is a simple yet interactive program that allows users to answer multiple-choice questions and track their score based on correct answers.

In this mini project, we use C++ programming concepts such as arrays, loops, and conditional statements to design a text-based quiz. It demonstrates user interaction, logic building, and the use of control structures effectively.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ğŸ’¡ 2. ABOUT THE PROJECT

The Quiz Game project is designed as a console-based program.
It displays a set of multiple-choice questions one by one, accepts the userâ€™s answer, and keeps track of the score.
At the end of the quiz, the total score is displayed with a performance message.

This project is:

Simple to understand and implement.

Perfect for learning basic logic and control flow in C++.

A fun and educational way to test programming skills.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ğŸ¯ 3. OBJECTIVES OF THE PROJECT

To develop a small interactive quiz game using C++.

To understand the use of arrays, loops, and decision-making statements.

To implement score tracking and question-answer validation.

To enhance logical thinking and coding practice through user-based input/output.

To demonstrate a simple example of a text-based interactive program.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
âš™ï¸ 4. FEATURES OF THE PROJECT

Displays multiple-choice questions to the user.

Tracks user score in real-time.

Displays final result and feedback.

Uses arrays for storing questions and answers.

Uses loops for iteration through multiple questions.

Fully console-based and easy to execute.âœ… 7. ADVANTAGES

Improves user interaction and logical understanding.

Easy to implement and extend (add more questions easily).

Provides instant feedback for each question.

Demonstrates clear use of arrays and control structures.

Helps beginners practice input/output and conditional logic.
